text: The headquarters of the State Migration Service in 2015 The State Migration Service of Ukraine () is a government agency of Ukraine that administers policy in the areas of immigration (both legal and illegal), emigration, and citizenship, as well as the resident registration (uk) system. It is part of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of Ukraine and was established in 2010. == References == Category:Ministry of Internal Affairs (Ukraine) Category:Government agencies established in 2010
title: State Migration Service (Ukraine)
